Bring a bridge up:

```bash
sudo ip link set lxdbr1 up

```

Give host an IP on private bridge:

```bash
sudo ip addr add 192.168.64.1/24 dev br64
sudo ip link set br64 up

```

Remove conflicting host IP on veth:

```bash
sudo ip addr del 192.168.64.2/24 dev veth-host

```

Enable forwarding:

```bash
echo 1 | sudo tee /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward
sudo sed -i 's/^#*net.ipv4.ip_forward.*/net.ipv4.ip_forward=1/' /etc/sysctl.conf
sudo sysctl -p

```

Add NAT (temporary; LXD normally manages this):

```bash
sudo iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -s 10.2.170.0/24 -o wlp2s0 -j MASQUERADE

```

Restart LXD daemon:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart snap.lxd.daemon

```

Netplan inside container (example for control plane):

```yaml
network:
  version: 2
  ethernets:
    eth0:
      dhcp4: true        # internet
    eth1:
      dhcp4: no         # private 5G net
      addresses:
        - 192.168.64.30/24

```

Apply:

```bash
sudo netplan apply

```

Create an LXD container (not VM) for SCTP support:

```bash
lxc launch ubuntu:22.04 vm1-cplane

```